-apprenticeship.html","media/img_20260508_114007_307.jpg","site-lib/scripts/graph-wasm.wasm","site-lib/fonts/70cc7ff27245e82ad414.ttf","site-lib/fonts/454577c22304619db035.ttf","site-lib/fonts/52ac8f3034507f1d9e53.ttf","site-lib/fonts/05b618077343fbbd92b7.ttf","site-lib/fonts/4bb6ac751d1c5478ff3a.woff2","site-lib/fonts/c504db5c06caaf7cdfba.woff2","site-lib/fonts/01dcbad1bac635f9c9cd.woff2","site-lib/media/6155340132a851f6089e.svg","site-lib/media/2308ab1944a6bfa5c5b8.svg","site-lib/html/file-tree-content.html","site-lib/scripts/webpage.js","site-lib/scripts/graph-wasm.js","site-lib/scripts/graph-render-worker.js","site-lib/media/favicon.png","site-lib/styles/obsidian.css","site-lib/styles/global-variable-styles.css","site-lib/styles/main-styles.css"],"webpages":{"1.-digital-twins-for-smarter-greenhouses.html":{"title":"1. Digital Twins for Smarter Greenhouses","icon":"","description":"(in Development)Designing an autonomous mobile solution (Mirte Master) for a group-based project (5 members) to monitor plant growth in a complex greenhouse environment. The system required high-precision mapping and safe navigation within narrow aisles and variable lighting conditions.\nPython\nGazebo\nROS2\nMachine Perception (YOLO)\n<img alt=\"IMG_20260508_114007_307.jpg\" src=\"media/img_20260508_114007_307.jpg\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 541px; max-width: 100%;\"><br><img alt=\"IMG_20260512_185203_410.jpg\" src=\"media/img_20260512_185203_410.jpg\" target=\"_self\">\n<br><a data-tooltip-position=\"top\" aria-label=\"https://studiegids.tudelft.nl/opleidingen/study-guide/educations/19060#/details/19481\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" class=\"external-link is-unresolved\" href=\"https://studiegids.tudelft.nl/opleidingen/study-guide/educations/19060#/details/19481\" target=\"_self\">Programme page</a> in the TU Delft Studyguide\n","aliases":[],"inlineTags":[],"frontmatterTags":[],"headers":[{"heading":"Context","level":3,"id":"Context_0"},{"heading":"Tools","level":3,"id":"Tools_0"},{"heading":"Images","level":3,"id":"Images_0"},{"heading":"Further Links","level":3,"id":"Further_Links_0"}],"links":[],"author":"","coverImageURL":"media/img_20260508_114007_307.jpg","fullURL":"1.-digital-twins-for-smarter-greenhouses.html","pathToRoot":".","attachments":["media/img_20260508_114007_307.jpg","media/img_20260512_185203_410.jpg"],"createdTime":1778485109510,"modifiedTime":1778697920087,"sourceSize":600,"sourcePath":"1. Digital Twins for Smarter Greenhouses.md","exportPath":"1.-digital-twins-for-smarter-greenhouses.html","showInTree":true,"treeOrder":0,"backlinks":["portfolio.html"],"type":"markdown"},"2.-sensor-fusion-using-3d-gaussian-splatting.html":{"title":"2. Sensor Fusion using 3D Gaussian Splatting","icon":"","description":"Gaussian Splatting for Object Detection using 4D Radar and Camera. In this work, we fused monocular camera data with 4D radar data in the feature space using a Gaussian representation. This was for the Advanced Machine Perception course. <img alt=\"Pasted image 20260511184210.png\" src=\"media/pasted-image-20260511184210.png\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 436px; max-width: 100%;\"> <br><img alt=\"Pasted image 20260511184242.png\" src=\"media/pasted-image-20260511184242.png\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 445px; max-width: 100%;\">\n<br><a data-tooltip-position=\"top\" aria-label=\"https://studiegids.tudelft.nl/opleidingen/study-guide/educations/19060#/details/19488\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" class=\"external-link is-unresolved\" href=\"https://studiegids.tudelft.nl/opleidingen/study-guide/educations/19060#/details/19488\" target=\"_self\">Programme page</a> in the TU Delft Studyguide\n<br>Final Assignment paper: <a data-tooltip-position=\"top\" aria-label=\"Report_Gaussian_miniCaR.pdf\" data-href=\"Report_Gaussian_miniCaR.pdf\" href=\"media/report_gaussian_minicar.html\" class=\"internal-link\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Gaussian miniCaR</a>\n","aliases":[],"inlineTags":[],"frontmatterTags":[],"headers":[{"heading":"Context","level":3,"id":"Context_0"},{"heading":"Images","level":3,"id":"Images_0"},{"heading":"Further Links","level":3,"id":"Further_Links_0"}],"links":["media/report_gaussian_minicar.html"],"author":"","coverImageURL":".","fullURL":"2.-sensor-fusion-using-3d-gaussian-splatting.html","pathToRoot":".","attachments":["media/pasted-image-20260511184210.png","media/pasted-image-20260511184242.png"],"createdTime":1778517235393,"modifiedTime":1778698118307,"sourceSize":580,"sourcePath":"2. Sensor Fusion using 3D Gaussian Splatting.md","exportPath":"2.-sensor-fusion-using-3d-gaussian-splatting.html","showInTree":true,"treeOrder":1,"backlinks":["portfolio.html"],"type":"markdown"},"3.-bachelor-thesis.html":{"title":"3. Bachelor Thesis","icon":"","description":"Comparison of Machine Learning Models for Generating Ship Movements. This includes analyzing the previously recorded data using drone controllers and processing them into learnable parameters. These predicted ship movements were later executed on a small movement platform that simulates the ship's movements in the lab (not part of the thesis).\nThis project was done in cooperation with the Fraunhofer Institute for Manufacturing Technology and Advanced Materials IFAM in Bremen.\nData processing Classical machine learning techniques\n<img alt=\"Pasted image 20260511174416.png\" src=\"media/pasted-image-20260511174416.png\" target=\"_self\"><br><img alt=\"Pasted image 20260511174436.png\" src=\"media/pasted-image-20260511174436.png\" target=\"_self\">\n<br><a data-tooltip-position=\"top\" aria-label=\"https://www.ifam.fraunhofer.de/en/Aboutus/Locations/Bremen.html\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" class=\"external-link is-unresolved\" href=\"https://www.ifam.fraunhofer.de/en/Aboutus/Locations/Bremen.html\" target=\"_self\">Fraunhofer IFAM in Bremen</a>\n<br><a data-tooltip-position=\"top\" aria-label=\"Bachelorarbeit.pdf\" data-href=\"Bachelorarbeit.pdf\" href=\"media/bachelorarbeit.html\" class=\"internal-link\" target=\"_self\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Bachelor Thesis Gunnar Martens</a>\n","aliases":[],"inlineTags":[],"frontmatterTags":[],"headers":[{"heading":"Context","level":3,"id":"Context_0"},{"heading":"Topics","level":3,"id":"Topics_0"},{"heading":"Images","level":3,"id":"Images_0"},{"heading":"Further Links","level":3,"id":"Further_Links_0"}],"links":["media/bachelorarbeit.html"],"author":"","coverImageURL":".","fullURL":"3.-bachelor-thesis.html","pathToRoot":".","attachments":["media/pasted-image-20260511174416.png","media/pasted-image-20260511174436.png"],"createdTime":1778485102625,"modifiedTime":1778698058090,"sourceSize":824,"sourcePath":"3. Bachelor Thesis.md","exportPath":"3.-bachelor-thesis.html","showInTree":true,"treeOrder":2,"backlinks":["portfolio.html"],"type":"markdown"},"4.-capability-extention-of-a-cobot.html":{"title":"4. Capability Extention of a Cobot","icon":"","description":"Modifying the Cobot system and extending the capabilities to make it use different endeffectors to spray a liquid on a predefined surface. This involved designing mechanical parts, rewiring internal electronics, Designing mechanical parts Solidworks Adding sensors and actuators to the cobot Pneumatic valve Programming the robot Internal block-diagram programming language Connection of different subsystems\n<img alt=\"IMG_20221025_112655_846.jpg\" src=\"images/img_20221025_112655_846.jpg\" target=\"_self\">\n<br><a data-tooltip-position=\"top\" aria-label=\"https://www.robotics-di.de/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" class=\"external-link is-unresolved\" href=\"https://www.robotics-di.de/\" target=\"_self\">Hahn Robotics Diepenau</a> (in German)\n","aliases":[],"inlineTags":[],"frontmatterTags":[],"headers":[{"heading":"Context","level":3,"id":"Context_0"},{"heading":"Tools","level":3,"id":"Tools_0"},{"heading":"Images","level":3,"id":"Images_0"},{"heading":"Further Links","level":3,"id":"Further_Links_0"}],"links":[],"author":"","coverImageURL":"images/img_20221025_112655_846.jpg","fullURL":"4.-capability-extention-of-a-cobot.html","pathToRoot":".","attachments":["images/img_20221025_112655_846.jpg","images/vid_20221124_145336.mp4"],"createdTime":1778514849120,"modifiedTime":1778516997909,"sourceSize":615,"sourcePath":"4. Capability Extention of a Cobot.md","exportPath":"4.-capability-extention-of-a-cobot.html","showInTree":true,"treeOrder":3,"backlinks":[],"type":"markdown"},"5.-plc-programming-student-job.html":{"title":"5. PLC Programming Student Job","icon":"","description":"Programming of a manufacturing plant simulator consisting of a small gantry crane style as part of an industrial manufacturing demonstrator. This device will be used to teach university students to work with and debug industrial grade infrastructure.\nPLC programming TIA Portal ST (structured text)\nFUB, KOP, ... Digital Communication protocols MQTT\nMonitoring in NodeRed Creation of electrical and logic plans EPLAN <img alt=\"-2147483648_-210156.jpg\" src=\"media/-2147483648_-210156.jpg\" target=\"_self\"><br><img alt=\"-2147483648_-210154.jpg\" src=\"media/-2147483648_-210154.jpg\" target=\"_self\">\n<br><a data-tooltip-position=\"top\" aria-label=\"https://www.hs-bremen.de/forschen/forschungs-und-transferprofil/forschungsprojekt/mobiler-lernkoffer-fuer-industrielle-kommunikation/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" class=\"external-link is-unresolved\" href=\"https://www.hs-bremen.de/forschen/forschungs-und-transferprofil/forschungsprojekt/mobiler-lernkoffer-fuer-industrielle-kommunikation/\" target=\"_self\">Project Page</a> at the Hochschule Bremen (in German)\n","aliases":[],"inlineTags":[],"frontmatterTags":[],"headers":[{"heading":"Context","level":3,"id":"Context_0"},{"heading":"Tools","level":3,"id":"Tools_0"},{"heading":"Images","level":3,"id":"Images_0"},{"heading":"Further Links","level":3,"id":"Further_Links_0"}],"links":[],"author":"","coverImageURL":"media/-2147483648_-210156.jpg","fullURL":"5.-plc-programming-student-job.html","pathToRoot":".","attachments":["media/-2147483648_-210156.jpg","media/-2147483648_-210154.jpg"],"createdTime":1778485109608,"modifiedTime":1778697770423,"sourceSize":744,"sourcePath":"5. PLC Programming Student Job.md","exportPath":"5.-plc-programming-student-job.html","showInTree":true,"treeOrder":4,"backlinks":["portfolio.html"],"type":"markdown"},"6.-final-examination-mechatronics-apprenticeship.html":{"title":"6. Final Examination Mechatronics Apprenticeship","icon":"","description":"Final Examination Part 2: Mechatronics (2020):\nThe final exam for this apprenticeship covered mechanical manufacturing, electrical wiring, PLC programming, system testing, and technical communication for mechatronics technicians.\nMechanical Manufacturing: Precision machining of components (drilling, countersinking, reaming) and assembly of complex assemblies according to technical drawings (e.g., fabrication of housing components).\nElectrical Engineering &amp; Wiring: Setup and wiring of control cabinets according to circuit diagrams while adhering to VDE standards; integration of sensors and actuators (e.g., illuminated pushbuttons, limit switches).\nAutomation Technology (PLC): Programming and optimization of control sequences; implementation of operating modes (manual/automatic) using GRAFCET and transfer to the target system (Beckhoff PLC).\nCommissioning &amp; System Testing: Systematic functional testing of mechatronic subsystems, troubleshooting, and documentation of test results.\nTechnical Communication: Explanation of technical relationships and process-related decisions in situational specialist discussions.\n<img alt=\"DSC_0333.JPG\" src=\"images/dsc_0333.jpg\" target=\"_self\" style=\"width: 339px; max-width: 100%;\">\n<br><a data-tooltip-position=\"top\" aria-label=\"https://www.harting.com/en-DE/apprenticeship\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" class=\"external-link is-unresolved\" href=\"https://www.harting.com/en-DE/apprenticeship\" target=\"_self\">Apprenticeships at Harting</a>\n<br><a data-tooltip-position=\"top\" aria-label=\"https://www.dqr.de/dqr/shareddocs/qualifikationen-neu/de/Mechatroniker-Mechatronikerin.html\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" class=\"external-link is-unresolved\" href=\"https://www.dqr.de/dqr/shareddocs/qualifikationen-neu/de/Mechatroniker-Mechatronikerin.html\" target=\"_self\">Mechatroniker</a> in the German Qualifications Framework (in German)\n<br><a data-tooltip-position=\"top\" aria-label=\"%5Bhttps://www.ihk.de/stuttgart/pal/mechatroniker-in-0942--5176024%5D(https://www.ihk.de/ostwestfalen/berufsbildung/ausbildung/berufe-a-z/mechatroniker-in-6782212)\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" class=\"external-link is-unresolved\" href=\"[https://www.ihk.de/stuttgart/pal/mechatroniker-in-0942--5176024](https://www.ihk.de/ostwestfalen/berufsbildung/ausbildung/berufe-a-z/mechatroniker-in-6782212)\" target=\"_self\">Mechatroniker</a> at the Bielefeld Chamber of Commerce and Industry (in German)\n","aliases":[],"inlineTags":[],"frontmatterTags":[],"headers":[{"heading":"Context","level":3,"id":"Context_0"},{"heading":"Tools","level":3,"id":"Tools_0"},{"heading":"Images","level":3,"id":"Images_0"},{"heading":"Further Links","level":3,"id":"Further_Links_0"}],"links":["%5Bhttps://www.ihk.de/stuttgart/pal/mechatroniker-in-0942--5176024%5D(https://www.ihk.de/ostwestfalen/berufsbildung/ausbildung/berufe-a-z/mechatroniker-in-6782212)"],"author":"","coverImageURL":"images/dsc_0333.jpg","fullURL":"6.-final-examination-mechatronics-apprenticeship.html","pathToRoot":".","attachments":["images/dsc_0333.jpg","images/mov_0067.mp4"],"createdTime":1778485109606,"modifiedTime":1778511096544,"sourceSize":1737,"sourcePath":"6. Final Examination Mechatronics Apprenticeship.md","exportPath":"6.-final-examination-mechatronics-apprenticeship.html","showInTree":true,"treeOrder":5,"backlinks":[],"type":"markdown"},"portfolio.html":{"title":"Portfolio","icon":"","description":"Designing an autonomous mobile solution (Mirte Master) for a group-based project (5 members) to monitor plant growth in a complex greenhouse environment. This project is still in development.Gaussian Splatting for Object Detection using 4D Radar and Camera.Comparison of Machine Learning Models for Generating Ship Movements.Modifying the Cobot system and extending the capabilities to make it use different endeffectors to spray a liquid on a predefined surface.Programming of a manufacturing plant simulator consisting of a small gantry crane style as part of an industrial manufacturing demonstrator. The final exam for this apprenticeship covers mechanical manufacturing, electrical wiring, PLC programming, system testing, and technical communication for mechatronics technicians.","aliases":[],"inlineTags":[],"frontmatterTags":[],"headers":[{"heading":"<a data-href=\"1. Digital Twins for Smarter Greenhouses\" href=\"1. Digital Twins for Smarter Greenhouses\" class=\"internal-link\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">1. Digital Twins for Smarter Greenhouses</a>","level":3,"id":"[[1._Digital_Twins_for_Smarter_Greenhouses]]_0"},{"heading":"<a data-href=\"2. Sensor Fusion using 3D Gaussian Splatting\" href=\"2. Sensor Fusion using 3D Gaussian Splatting\" class=\"internal-link\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">2. Sensor Fusion using 3D Gaussian Splatting</a>","level":3,"id":"[[2._Sensor_Fusion_using_3D_Gaussian_Splatting]]_0"},{"heading":"<a data-href=\"3. Bachelor Thesis\" href=\"3. Bachelor Thesis\" class=\"internal-link\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">3. Bachelor Thesis</a>","level":3,"id":"[[3._Bachelor_Thesis]]_0"},{"heading":"<a data-href=\"4. Capability Extention of a Cobot\" href=\"4. Capability Extention of a Cobot\" class=\"internal-link\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">4. Capability Extention of a Cobot</a>","level":3,"id":"[[4._Capability_Extention_of_a_Cobot]]_0"},{"heading":"<a data-href=\"5. PLC Programming Student Job\" href=\"5. PLC Programming Student Job\" class=\"internal-link\" target=\"_blank\" rel